When you create a DOM tree you usually don't set namespaces by adding an
attribute "xmlns" but use the nsURI member of DOM nodes. This patch adds the
capability to serialize namespaces to TextWriter. Further it adds NS support to
DocumentImpl.importNode.

please check this part of the patch:
     public Element createElementNS(String namespaceURI, String qualifiedName) {
-        return new ElementImpl(this, qualifiedName);
+        return new ElementImpl(this, qualifiedName, namespaceURI);
     }
All testcases of test-unit run well but as the variable is a *qualified*Name, it
might cause problems. I don't expect them but you are better into the code than
I am.
